    "description": "<p><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW256382589 BCX2\" data-ccp-parastyle=\"Ars Magica Text\" data-ccp-parastyle-defn=\"{\"ObjectId\":\"5a36acb2-12ef-4854-81b3-2dc8f29e2832|221\",\"ClassId\":1073872969,\"Properties\":[469777841,\"Times New Roman\",469777843,\"Times New Roman\",469777844,\"Times New Roman\",469769226,\"Times New Roman\",268442635,\"24\",469777842,\"Times New Roman\",469775450,\"Ars Magica Text\",201340122,\"2\",134233614,\"true\",469778129,\"ArsMagicaText\",335572020,\"99\",335559738,\"117\",469778324,\"Normal\"]}\"><span style=\"font-family: Times, 'Times_EmbeddedFont', 'Times_MSFontService', Times New Roman, serif\">The character is trained in the New Aristotle, having received his instruction from a teac</span></span><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW256382589 BCX2\" data-ccp-parastyle=\"Ars Magica Text\"><span style=\"font-family: Times, 'Times_EmbeddedFont', 'Times_MSFontService', Times New Roman, serif\">her using recently translated texts of Aristotle in preference to the normal curriculum. The character gains a +1 bonus on Artes Liberales rolls for grammar, logic, and rhetoric, as well as a +1 bonus when calculating Disputatio Totals (see <em>Art and Academe, </em>page 103,<em> </em>for details). A magus with this Virtue may add +1 to his Lab Totals if attempting to synthesize the New Aristotle with Magic Theory (as described on page 11 of <em>Art and Academe</em>). This Virtue is compatible with Puissant Artes Liberales.</span></span></p>",
